org.osgi.cdi.api.extension.events
Class InterBundleEvent

java.lang.Object
  org.osgi.cdi.api.extension.events.InterBundleEvent

public class InterBundleEvent
extends Object

This class represents a communication event between bean bundles.

It allows to specify:

  • The message as an Object,

  • The type of the message as a Class,

  • The origin of the message (within or outside the bundle).

It may be used in javax.enterprise.event.Observes method in order to listen inter-bundle communications.

Author:
Mathieu ANCELIN - SERLI (mathieu.ancelin@serli.com), Matthieu CLOCHARD - SERLI (matthieu.clochard@serli.com)
